      "text": "Kachi ghani means the seed is crushed slowly at low temperature — no added heat, no solvents, no bleaching or deodorising — so the colour, aroma and the seed's natural compounds stay intact. Refined oils, by contrast, are heat- or solvent-extracted and then degummed, bleached and deodorised, which strips out most of the smell and colour."
